# UI/UX Components Guidelines

## Design System
USE Shadcn/ui!

### Color Palette
- Primary: Modern, professional colors suitable for beauty/fashion industry
- Secondary: Complementary colors for accents
- Neutral: Grays for text and backgrounds
- Success/Error: Clear feedback colors

### Typography
- Use Geist font family (already configured)
- Maintain consistent font weights and sizes
- Ensure good readability across devices

## Component Architecture

### Core Components

```typescript
// src/components/ui/Button.tsx
interface ButtonProps {
  variant: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'outline' | 'ghost';
  size: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  isLoading?: boolean;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

// src/components/ui/Card.tsx
interface CardProps {
  title?: string;
  description?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

// src/components/ui/LoadingSpinner.tsx
interface LoadingSpinnerProps {
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  text?: string;
}
```

### Feature-Specific Components

```typescript
// src/components/ImageUploader.tsx
interface ImageUploaderProps {
  onImageSelect: (file: File) => void;
  onError: (error: string) => void;
  isLoading?: boolean;
  maxSize?: number;
  acceptedTypes?: string[];
}

// src/components/HairstyleCard.tsx
interface HairstyleCardProps {
  imageUrl: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  difficulty: 'Easy' | 'Medium' | 'Hard';
  maintenance: 'Low' | 'Medium' | 'High';
}

// src/components/FaceShapeIndicator.tsx
interface FaceShapeIndicatorProps {
  faceShape: string;
  confidence: number;
}
```

## Layout Guidelines

### Page Structure
- Header with app branding
- Main content area with clear hierarchy
- Footer with additional information
- Responsive design for mobile and desktop

### Grid System
- Use CSS Grid for complex layouts
- Flexbox for component alignment
- Tailwind's responsive utilities for breakpoints

## User Experience Patterns

### Loading States
- Skeleton loaders for content
- Progress indicators for uploads
- Spinner animations for AI processing

### Error Handling
- Toast notifications for errors
- Inline error messages for forms
- Fallback UI for failed states

### Success States
- Confirmation messages
- Visual feedback for completed actions
- Celebration animations for results

## Accessibility Requirements

### ARIA Labels
- Proper labeling for screen readers
- Descriptive alt text for images
- Keyboard navigation support

### Color Contrast
- WCAG AA compliance
- High contrast mode support
- Color-blind friendly palette

### Focus Management
- Visible focus indicators
- Logical tab order
- Skip links for navigation

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints
- Mobile: 320px - 768px
- Tablet: 768px - 1024px
- Desktop: 1024px+

### Mobile-First Approach
- Design for mobile first
- Progressive enhancement for larger screens
- Touch-friendly interface elements

## Animation Guidelines

### Micro-interactions
- Subtle hover effects
- Smooth transitions between states
- Loading animations that don't distract

### Performance
- Use CSS transforms for animations
- Avoid animating layout properties
- Implement reduced motion preferences

## Component Library

### shadcn/ui Integration
- Use shadcn/ui components as base
- Customize components to match brand
- Extend components for specific needs

### Custom Components
- Create reusable components for app-specific features
- Maintain consistent API patterns
- Document component props and usage